WEBVTT



00:00:18.498 --> 00:00:21.626
H-Hello! I'm Super Scrappy Seiichi!

00:00:26.756 --> 00:00:31.511
A love at first sight… kind of thing.

00:00:31.594 --> 00:00:33.388
Oh…

00:00:34.889 --> 00:00:36.057
Um…

00:00:39.352 --> 00:00:42.730
Let's start off as friends… kind of thing.

00:01:02.876 --> 00:01:04.169
Seiichi?

00:01:11.217 --> 00:01:13.553
-This is the best way to carry it.
-No way.

00:01:13.636 --> 00:01:16.181
You look like a beetle from this angle.

00:01:16.264 --> 00:01:19.434
-Seiichi. Hurry up.
-Okay.

00:01:19.517 --> 00:01:20.476
-Go!
-All right!

00:01:20.560 --> 00:01:22.604
Go, Seiichi! You can do it!

00:01:22.687 --> 00:01:24.105
-Super scrappy!
-Huh?

00:01:24.189 --> 00:01:26.191
-Super scrappy!
-What?

00:01:26.274 --> 00:01:27.859
Super scrappy!

00:01:27.942 --> 00:01:28.776
Yay!

00:01:33.448 --> 00:01:35.408
I'll take your marriage registration form.

00:01:35.491 --> 00:01:36.826
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

00:01:36.910 --> 00:01:38.494
Congratulations.

00:01:38.578 --> 00:01:40.872
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

00:01:40.955 --> 00:01:42.707
-Yes!
-Yeah.

00:01:44.125 --> 00:01:46.711
I'm looking forward to our life together.

00:01:48.296 --> 00:01:49.297
Yeah.

00:01:50.548 --> 00:01:51.758
Ready?

00:01:52.884 --> 00:01:54.761
Say cheese.

00:02:00.934 --> 00:02:04.354
Oh, man! I just thought of something!

00:02:04.437 --> 00:02:06.689
Wouldn't "Kanau" be a great name?

00:02:20.536 --> 00:02:21.537
I'm home.

00:02:29.254 --> 00:02:33.591
JULY 4TH, 2018

00:02:33.675 --> 00:02:35.593
Please come closer.

00:02:50.775 --> 00:02:52.986
We will now close the door.

00:02:53.861 --> 00:02:56.197
Please say your final farewells.

00:02:58.574 --> 00:02:59.993
Seiichi.

00:03:02.412 --> 00:03:03.538
Seiichi.

00:03:27.437 --> 00:03:31.357
He was such a kind boy.

00:03:36.321 --> 00:03:39.782
Why did this have to happen?

00:03:44.620 --> 00:03:46.873
We all got to see him off, didn't we?

00:03:49.459 --> 00:03:52.003
It wasn't all of us.

00:03:57.550 --> 00:03:59.093
I'm sorry

00:04:00.345 --> 00:04:03.639
that my relatives were unable to attend.

00:04:07.352 --> 00:04:09.270
What could you do?

00:04:11.439 --> 00:04:14.567
They must have better things to do.

00:04:14.650 --> 00:04:15.985
Hush.

00:04:23.117 --> 00:04:26.537
What will you do about the baby?

00:04:29.582 --> 00:04:32.960
I will raise the baby with care.

00:04:33.461 --> 00:04:37.924
But wouldn't it be hard on your own?

00:04:38.758 --> 00:04:44.722
You probably don't have many people
in Tokyo who can help you.

00:04:45.973 --> 00:04:47.058
How about this?

00:04:47.141 --> 00:04:52.730
You can quit your job
and raise the baby with us in Fukuoka.

00:04:58.444 --> 00:05:00.655
Thank you, but…

00:05:01.948 --> 00:05:05.201
I'm not quitting my job.

00:05:06.786 --> 00:05:09.205
I'll figure things out on my own…

00:05:10.915 --> 00:05:16.629
Raising a child is no easy task.

00:05:18.714 --> 00:05:23.719
Your mother was too busy
to attend her son-in-law's funeral.

00:05:24.387 --> 00:05:29.934
She won't offer you any help, will she?

00:05:30.017 --> 00:05:30.935
Don't say that.

00:05:31.018 --> 00:05:32.353
What?

00:05:43.739 --> 00:05:44.740
I'll be fine.

00:05:48.828 --> 00:05:50.329
"Fine"?

00:05:54.041 --> 00:05:58.504
The child of our dearest son

00:05:58.588 --> 00:06:02.383
is a precious grandchild to us.

00:06:04.218 --> 00:06:05.636
Sumiko.

00:06:06.220 --> 00:06:09.891
What I'm saying is,
your child isn't just yours alone.

00:06:11.976 --> 00:06:15.938
You need to give that a lot of thought.

00:06:16.022 --> 00:06:17.648
Otherwise…

00:06:19.650 --> 00:06:23.321
it's your child who will end up
going through hardship.

00:06:36.209 --> 00:06:40.505
Funerals in Japan are quiet.

00:06:42.006 --> 00:06:43.090
Yeah.

00:06:44.008 --> 00:06:47.803
In Korea, it's a lot noisier.

00:06:50.765 --> 00:06:55.686
We cry out loud more, drink alcohol,

00:06:57.396 --> 00:07:01.734
share memories, and get drunk.

00:07:05.655 --> 00:07:07.114
I see.

00:07:10.910 --> 00:07:15.623
I'm sure Seiichi would want…

00:07:18.834 --> 00:07:22.338
everyone to live happily.

00:07:25.049 --> 00:07:26.425
You're right.

00:07:30.388 --> 00:07:35.101
The ones left behind have to go on…

00:07:37.103 --> 00:07:40.314
living happy, fulfilling lives.

00:07:44.318 --> 00:07:45.444
Right?

00:07:56.080 --> 00:07:58.207
Let’s go home and share a few drinks.

00:08:10.094 --> 00:08:11.429
Let's drink.

00:08:17.768 --> 00:08:21.022
Ms. Sasaki, would you like some potatoes?

00:08:21.105 --> 00:08:23.065
All right. Here.

00:08:23.149 --> 00:08:25.484
It's okay. Here, let's eat.

00:08:28.029 --> 00:08:29.739
Ms. Sasaki.

00:08:29.822 --> 00:08:33.159
They're warm and tasty, you know.

00:08:34.535 --> 00:08:35.870
Here.

00:08:38.581 --> 00:08:40.333
Don't take too long, okay?

00:08:40.416 --> 00:08:43.252
We have many other residents
who need help too.

00:08:43.336 --> 00:08:44.462
Yes, sir.

00:08:46.255 --> 00:08:47.256
Yes, sir.

00:08:50.509 --> 00:08:52.720
Here. Try the fish.

00:09:00.811 --> 00:09:02.229
Are you okay?

00:09:02.855 --> 00:09:05.650
You have time to worry about others, huh?

00:09:07.360 --> 00:09:08.569
I'm sorry.

00:09:11.822 --> 00:09:13.240
I'm fine.

00:09:20.623 --> 00:09:23.376
Caregiving is a good job, don't you think?

00:09:24.669 --> 00:09:25.628
Huh?

00:09:26.879 --> 00:09:27.922
Never mind.

00:09:28.422 --> 00:09:29.256
Bye.

00:09:36.972 --> 00:09:38.641
Good work today.

00:09:50.528 --> 00:09:51.570
I'm home.

00:09:52.154 --> 00:09:53.364
Welcome home.

00:09:57.576 --> 00:09:59.578
Whoa. Thanks.

00:09:59.662 --> 00:10:00.663
Yeah.

00:10:19.724 --> 00:10:22.351
What? Aren't you gonna eat?

00:10:23.310 --> 00:10:24.812
Yeah, I will.

00:10:26.313 --> 00:10:27.898
Thanks for the meal.

00:10:29.150 --> 00:10:30.526
Eat it with the bread.

00:10:30.609 --> 00:10:31.944
-This?
-Yeah.

00:10:38.075 --> 00:10:40.619
Mm, this is good.

00:10:50.671 --> 00:10:54.550
Are you in touch with Sumiko?

00:10:56.218 --> 00:10:57.428
Kind of.

00:10:59.096 --> 00:11:00.765
How has she been lately?

00:11:02.975 --> 00:11:07.062
Her company allows her
to take maternity and childcare leave.

00:11:07.730 --> 00:11:12.067
She can take time off,
so she said she'd be okay.

00:11:14.862 --> 00:11:16.530
But that can't be true, huh?

00:11:22.953 --> 00:11:24.997
How about we go visit soon?

00:11:29.001 --> 00:11:30.419
Let's go see Sumiko.

00:12:16.507 --> 00:12:17.925
We're coming in.

00:12:33.816 --> 00:12:35.234
Sumiko.

00:12:37.111 --> 00:12:38.571
Ryu?

00:12:40.531 --> 00:12:42.324
And Johan too?

00:12:43.117 --> 00:12:46.287
Wait. Was the door unlocked?

00:12:46.370 --> 00:12:47.371
Yeah.

00:12:49.915 --> 00:12:51.333
Sorry about the mess.

00:12:52.042 --> 00:12:54.253
I'll clean up, so just give me a second.

00:13:07.308 --> 00:13:09.518
It's fine. Don't mind us.

00:13:14.356 --> 00:13:15.608
What do you mean?

00:13:18.110 --> 00:13:19.111
Huh?

00:13:20.029 --> 00:13:21.655
What do you mean, "it's fine"?

00:13:22.865 --> 00:13:23.699
Uh…

00:13:23.782 --> 00:13:26.744
-I mean--
-It must be nice having Johan with you.

00:13:27.411 --> 00:13:28.495
Huh?

00:13:28.579 --> 00:13:30.289
You're not alone.

00:13:31.373 --> 00:13:33.292
You're not lonely.

00:13:34.084 --> 00:13:35.085
Huh?

00:13:35.878 --> 00:13:37.254
It's not fair.

00:13:38.339 --> 00:13:39.965
Isn't this messed up?

00:13:41.967 --> 00:13:43.052
Why?

00:13:55.814 --> 00:13:58.901
Why did Seiichi have to die?

00:14:02.446 --> 00:14:04.615
I don't get it.

00:14:05.324 --> 00:14:08.702
I just don't get it at all.

00:14:13.290 --> 00:14:14.458
Sumiko.

00:14:17.670 --> 00:14:20.506
You could ask your family for help.

00:14:20.589 --> 00:14:22.925
I don't have any family.

00:14:25.052 --> 00:14:26.679
I mean,

00:14:27.805 --> 00:14:32.059
if he was gonna leave me by myself,
he shouldn't have married me.

00:14:35.020 --> 00:14:36.563
And a baby, on top of that?

00:14:36.647 --> 00:14:39.650
A b-baby…

00:14:40.401 --> 00:14:41.652
Why?

00:14:44.780 --> 00:14:48.158
If he was gonna leave
the two of us behind…

00:14:50.661 --> 00:14:52.287
then…

00:15:02.214 --> 00:15:03.549
Calm down.

00:15:05.342 --> 00:15:08.929
I can't become a mother.

00:15:11.598 --> 00:15:14.018
Someone like me,
raised by a mother like that,

00:15:14.727 --> 00:15:17.688
could never become a parent.

00:15:20.190 --> 00:15:21.608
Sumiko.

00:15:26.030 --> 00:15:27.448
You're not alone.

00:15:29.658 --> 00:15:32.578
My mom and dad

00:15:33.954 --> 00:15:35.998
care about you too.

00:15:45.758 --> 00:15:50.012
How about we make a trip to Nasu together?

00:16:22.211 --> 00:16:24.546
All right, we're here.

00:16:26.799 --> 00:16:29.218
Wow, it's been a while.

00:16:33.597 --> 00:16:34.932
Okay.

00:16:35.015 --> 00:16:37.643
-All right.
-Leave the bags to me.

00:16:37.726 --> 00:16:39.895
-What? Can you handle them?
-Yeah.

00:16:40.521 --> 00:16:42.940
-There.
-You're so strong.

00:16:45.359 --> 00:16:46.735
Welcome home.

00:16:46.819 --> 00:16:48.112
I'm home.

00:16:48.612 --> 00:16:50.864
Tadashi is still at work.

00:16:50.948 --> 00:16:53.033
I'm sure he'll be back soon.

00:16:53.784 --> 00:16:55.160
-It's been a while, huh?
-Yeah.

00:16:55.244 --> 00:16:56.870
Hey, wait. The key.

00:16:56.954 --> 00:16:57.955
Oh, right.

00:16:58.038 --> 00:16:59.456
-Here.
-Thanks.

00:17:20.853 --> 00:17:21.854
There.

00:17:23.147 --> 00:17:26.859
That house with the red roof
is where my family lives.

00:17:29.736 --> 00:17:31.822
We're family after all.

00:17:33.532 --> 00:17:34.992
And sometimes,

00:17:36.743 --> 00:17:39.037
being family makes it harder
to rely on them.

00:17:57.806 --> 00:17:59.224
You sure eat a lot.

00:17:59.308 --> 00:18:01.602
-Johan, do you want more somen?
-Yes, please.

00:18:01.685 --> 00:18:02.978
Coming right up.

00:18:04.188 --> 00:18:05.939
-He can really eat.
-Yeah.

00:18:06.023 --> 00:18:08.483
Do you have somen like this in Korea too?

00:18:08.567 --> 00:18:10.861
-Yeah, we have the noodles.
-Yeah?

00:18:10.944 --> 00:18:14.072
But we don't dip them in tsuyu like this.

00:18:14.156 --> 00:18:15.282
-One serving each?
-Yeah.

00:18:15.365 --> 00:18:17.326
-Oh, I see.
-We each get our own bowl.

00:18:17.409 --> 00:18:19.870
-Sumiko, are you able to eat?
-Yeah.

00:18:19.953 --> 00:18:21.288
-I'm eating.
-Eat a lot, okay?

00:18:21.371 --> 00:18:22.706
Thank you.

00:18:22.789 --> 00:18:24.666
Your nasu is the best, Auntie.

00:18:24.750 --> 00:18:26.043
-Really?
-Yeah.

00:18:26.126 --> 00:18:28.921
-Yeah, it's good.
-No place like Nasu for nasu.

00:18:29.004 --> 00:18:31.256
Whoa, you learned stuff like that too?

00:18:31.340 --> 00:18:32.341
Yeah.

00:19:42.160 --> 00:19:43.161
Hey.

00:19:43.704 --> 00:19:45.956
What? Hurry up and get changed.

00:19:46.039 --> 00:19:47.791
But it's still four o'clock.

00:19:47.874 --> 00:19:50.210
That's when the fish are biting.

00:19:50.794 --> 00:19:52.504
You wanna catch euneo, Johan?

00:19:52.587 --> 00:19:53.964
Right? Let's go fishing!

00:19:54.047 --> 00:19:56.675
Hey, come on. Get ready.

00:19:56.758 --> 00:19:59.052
-Come on. Let's go fishing!
-Okay, okay.

00:19:59.636 --> 00:20:01.722
-Let's go.
-It's so early.

00:20:01.805 --> 00:20:03.515
We're gonna catch euneo!

00:20:19.448 --> 00:20:20.657
They're not biting, huh?

00:20:22.409 --> 00:20:25.287
The fish won't be caught that easily.

00:20:25.787 --> 00:20:27.372
Okay.

00:20:45.223 --> 00:20:46.433
Thank you.

00:20:47.559 --> 00:20:49.102
Huh? For what?

00:20:50.645 --> 00:20:54.608
Back when I quit ice hockey,

00:20:55.108 --> 00:20:56.818
thank you for not saying anything.

00:20:59.613 --> 00:21:01.490
What's this, all of a sudden?

00:21:10.665 --> 00:21:11.708
Oh!

00:21:11.792 --> 00:21:13.418
I got a bite!

00:21:14.753 --> 00:21:16.380
-Where?
-Don't panic.

00:21:16.463 --> 00:21:20.133
Reel it in slowly. Good.

00:21:20.217 --> 00:21:22.052
-Whoa!
-Keep going. Just like that.

00:21:22.135 --> 00:21:24.054
It's here! Can I pull it in now?

00:21:24.137 --> 00:21:27.557
-All right.
-There. It's in!

00:21:27.641 --> 00:21:29.267
Look at that!

00:21:30.727 --> 00:21:31.812
Johan!

00:21:32.312 --> 00:21:33.313
Yeah!

00:21:35.023 --> 00:21:36.608
-Look!
-Whoa!

00:21:36.691 --> 00:21:38.777
-Sweetfish.
-Wow.

00:21:38.860 --> 00:21:41.696
-Euneo?
-Yeah, euneo. This is amazing.

00:21:43.323 --> 00:21:44.366
-Whoa.
-Whoa.

00:21:44.449 --> 00:21:46.243
-It was a bit weak.
-Impressive.

00:21:46.326 --> 00:21:47.327
Whoa.

00:21:47.411 --> 00:21:49.329
-Just a bit more.
-Too weak.

00:21:49.955 --> 00:21:51.248
Go!

00:21:51.331 --> 00:21:52.916
-Wow!
-Wow!

00:21:52.999 --> 00:21:56.044
-How's that?
-Amazing! It skipped a lot.

00:21:56.128 --> 00:21:58.046
-All right.
-Wow, the Narutaki family.

00:22:03.468 --> 00:22:05.679
-Whoa, that was amazing.
-Wow.

00:22:05.762 --> 00:22:06.805
Nice one.

00:22:39.671 --> 00:22:40.881
Did you sleep well?

00:22:41.715 --> 00:22:43.425
-Yeah.
-Good.

00:22:44.426 --> 00:22:46.678
-That's…
-Mm-hmm.

00:22:47.179 --> 00:22:49.473
Brings back memories.

00:22:52.350 --> 00:22:56.188
You were cute since you were little.

00:22:59.733 --> 00:23:03.945
My mother didn't care about me at all,

00:23:04.446 --> 00:23:08.617
so maybe that's why I got to go
to so many places with you guys instead.

00:23:12.579 --> 00:23:13.914
Sumiko.

00:23:19.794 --> 00:23:24.007
Would you like to
have your child here with us?

00:23:28.470 --> 00:23:29.721
What?

00:23:29.804 --> 00:23:34.976
Things like blood relations are a curse.

00:23:36.019 --> 00:23:38.355
Being family doesn't mean
you understand each other.

00:23:39.606 --> 00:23:42.317
That's just wishful thinking.

00:23:45.153 --> 00:23:46.571
I…

00:23:48.323 --> 00:23:50.325
I was like that

00:23:51.451 --> 00:23:53.119
with my parents too.

00:23:54.496 --> 00:23:59.709
You and your mother

00:24:01.044 --> 00:24:02.879
are nothing alike.

00:24:06.424 --> 00:24:08.677
You don't need to worry about a thing.

00:24:09.719 --> 00:24:10.720
Okay?

00:24:12.889 --> 00:24:18.395
You're always welcome in our home.

00:24:20.814 --> 00:24:23.400
We may not be blood-related…

00:24:26.111 --> 00:24:28.572
but you'll always have a home with us.

00:24:33.201 --> 00:24:34.202
Right?

00:24:35.412 --> 00:24:36.413
Oh!

00:24:38.331 --> 00:24:39.332
Yes, okay.

00:24:40.083 --> 00:24:41.626
It's your home.

00:24:44.421 --> 00:24:45.422
Yeah.

00:24:52.971 --> 00:24:54.139
I…

00:24:55.974 --> 00:24:57.434
I've been given so much

00:24:58.935 --> 00:25:01.521
by so many people.

00:25:09.446 --> 00:25:10.780
This guy too.

00:25:11.865 --> 00:25:13.491
He's given me a lot.

00:25:39.517 --> 00:25:40.727
Sumiko.

00:25:44.439 --> 00:25:45.857
Why don't you…

00:25:48.526 --> 00:25:50.195
come live with us?

00:25:52.989 --> 00:25:53.990
What?

00:26:04.417 --> 00:26:05.919
That's what I want too.

00:26:27.732 --> 00:26:29.609
The baby's name.

00:26:32.696 --> 00:26:33.822
It's Kanau.

00:26:38.118 --> 00:26:39.536
Kanau?

00:26:44.290 --> 00:26:49.212
It's written with characters that mean
"dreams come true" and "universe."

00:26:50.714 --> 00:26:51.923
Kanau.

00:26:56.720 --> 00:26:59.931
Super Scrappy Seiichi came up with it.

00:27:37.552 --> 00:27:39.053
All right.

00:28:38.029 --> 00:28:39.656
The baby was delivered safely.

00:28:40.156 --> 00:28:42.700
Please wait while we complete
some procedures.

00:28:45.161 --> 00:28:48.248
The mother is recovering well too.

00:28:49.749 --> 00:28:51.835
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

00:28:59.717 --> 00:29:01.803
Man, the baby is here.

00:29:01.886 --> 00:29:03.471
It's here, huh?

00:29:04.806 --> 00:29:05.723
What a relief.

00:29:05.807 --> 00:29:09.018
Oh, man. Kanau.

00:29:10.353 --> 00:29:11.771
Wow.

00:29:26.202 --> 00:29:28.121
-Kanau.
-Kanau.

00:29:28.204 --> 00:29:29.539
Kanau.

00:29:30.039 --> 00:29:30.874
Wow.

00:29:30.957 --> 00:29:32.000
So small.

00:29:32.083 --> 00:29:34.794
So wrinkly. Cute.

00:29:35.461 --> 00:29:37.463
-Kanau.
-Oh, she smiled!

00:29:37.547 --> 00:29:39.340
-Kanau!
-You smiled!

00:29:39.424 --> 00:29:41.175
Over here. Peekaboo!

00:29:41.259 --> 00:29:43.970
-Here! She's looking this way!
-She looked this way.

00:29:44.053 --> 00:29:44.971
-Kanau!
-Kanau!

00:29:45.054 --> 00:29:46.264
-Is she looking?
-Yeah.

00:29:46.347 --> 00:29:47.432
-Is she?
-She is.

00:29:47.515 --> 00:29:49.767
-Kanau!
-You're incredible!

00:29:49.851 --> 00:29:50.810
-Hello.
-So cute.

00:29:50.894 --> 00:29:52.896
-Do you see us, Kanau?
-She smiled.

00:29:52.979 --> 00:29:58.818
-Ryu is setting up the crib for us.
-There we go.

00:29:58.902 --> 00:30:00.904
Isn't that great, Kanau?

00:30:00.987 --> 00:30:02.739
-Kanau!
-Kanau, look over here.

00:30:02.822 --> 00:30:03.823
Over here.

00:30:06.826 --> 00:30:08.953
Johan got you a toy.

00:30:09.037 --> 00:30:09.913
Argh!

00:30:09.996 --> 00:30:11.956
-Huh? Ryu, are you okay?
-Keep it down!

00:30:12.040 --> 00:30:13.249
Help me out.

00:30:13.333 --> 00:30:15.752
-You gotta stick this in. This one.
-Okay.

00:30:15.835 --> 00:30:17.921
-Down there.
-Okay.

00:30:19.464 --> 00:30:20.924
-Ready?
-Okay.

00:30:23.801 --> 00:30:26.387
Huh?

00:30:27.722 --> 00:30:28.806
Yes, we did it!

00:30:29.849 --> 00:30:36.397
The stars shining above us
have created countless stories.

00:30:37.690 --> 00:30:42.320
One of them is loved all across Japan.

00:30:42.403 --> 00:30:44.572
Night on the Galactic Railroad.

00:30:44.656 --> 00:30:45.615
Kanau.

00:30:45.698 --> 00:30:47.116
"Campanella."

00:30:47.617 --> 00:30:50.828
"It's just the two of us alone again."

00:30:52.080 --> 00:30:54.165
"Let's go on together, as far as we can."

00:30:54.832 --> 00:30:56.793
"I'm no longer afraid."

00:30:58.086 --> 00:31:03.508
"Just like that scorpion,
if it's truly for everyone's happiness,

00:31:04.550 --> 00:31:08.763
I don't care what happens to my body."

00:31:10.139 --> 00:31:11.140
"Yes."

00:31:12.183 --> 00:31:13.893
"I feel the same way."

00:31:15.144 --> 00:31:16.145
"But I wonder…"

00:31:17.271 --> 00:31:20.984
"What is true happiness?"

00:31:22.485 --> 00:31:26.114
"I still don't know."

00:31:27.782 --> 00:31:29.117
I know what it is.

00:31:30.076 --> 00:31:30.910
Hmm?

00:31:36.791 --> 00:31:37.792
Right?

00:33:56.472 --> 00:33:59.392
Subtitle translation by: Remi Miura